{"questionId":"79be5180","correctAnswer":"3","section":"Math","steps":[{"title":"Solve the system by substitution","content":"Substitute $y=9x+12$ into $x+7y=20$: $$x + 7(9x+12) = 20 \\Rightarrow 64x = -64 \\Rightarrow x = -1.$$"},{"title":"Find $y$","content":"Then $y = 9(-1)+12 = 3$. The answer is <strong>3</strong>."}]}